originalText: cc_dh_zonerMa
Start Element
zonerMa
You keep those filthy paws away from me, pipe-jammin' scum! Or I'll...

::An ancient, shriveled woman angrily waves her ladle at you.::

Pipeworkin' sons of drop-offs! If I wanted some zone-ass bastards a-bargin' into my home, I would've never left the Drop Zone.
context.npc_xpbl_cc_dh_zonerMa_intimidateSuccess
You $(#boys/folks) leave this place now, you! Or else Imma open a can of zone-out and show ya how this grandma dominates pipelickers like you. Beat it now, y'all!
context.loc_cc_knowDropZone

Excuse me, man, but this place used to be mine, you know. So you're actually a-bargin' into *my* place, you... you... nasty woman. We just need to, like, find something important and we're, like, gone.

Whatcha say, dross-face? Your place? GET OUTTA HERE!

You too, $(#barrel-stuffer/pipe-scutchin' hooksie).
Hey, w-who are you call-ing a $(#barrel-stuffer/pipe-scutchin' hooksie), you smelly crone?
English

I am... My partner a-and I are here on official P-Praetorian Security business. Mhm. Y-you are to step aside and let us, um, do our s-search, or el... else I'll be forced to d-detain you... and stuff.

::[Persuade]:: I am... My partner a-and I are here on official P-Praetorian Security business. Mhm. Y-you are to step aside and let us, um, do our s-search, or el... else I'll be forced to d-detain you... and stuff.
::[Intimidate]:: Unless you... y-you want to be the main ingredient of that, um, soup you're m-making, you're go-ing to let us... search this-s-s place.

::[Persuade]:: Please, ma'am, pl-ease. This m-m-man here has b-been trying to... uh... recover his fa-ther's t-techwatch for ten years! It's... the only thing... um... his fa-ther left him. H-have you no heart? It's been stashed some-where in your... your... house, ma'am. P-please let us, oh, search f-for it.
H-how about we give you a few ch-charons for your trouble? W-would it then be okay for us to take a peek-k-k?
Step a-aside, Dude - I'm gonna solve this MY way. ::Burp and attack!::
Shut up, you rail-grindin' trash surfer!
English
Eh...
English
Eh... Praetorians?
Ya lyin' pipelicker.

::Her defenses buckle under pressure, and her piercing gaze turns dull.::

Alright... Alright.

It is you who is gonna be in this soup once I shove this ladle up your drop hole, $(#barrel-stuffer/pipe-scutchin' hooksie). I've seen and heard things you'd never believe durin' this long life o' mine, and your threats don't scare me one bit!
Father's techwatch? Like... wrist watch? I haven't found no watch in here, and I've been here for plenty a years now.

::Her eyes flare up.::

Charons...? What are ya a-offerin' exactly?
::[Intelligence]:: W-wrinkly guano-slurping sow!
S-s-stupid old woman.
Hag!
No, you are a r-rail-grindin' tr-tr-tr... what w-as it?
Uh, I don't know how to top that...

You enforcers are the scum o' the earth! Where were you when my husband was bein' stabbed by a derailed madman at the metro station? Where were you when the Zone was a-riotin' and innocent people were bein' zoned out?
praem
You ain't a-foolin' me!
Just be quick and don't make no mess. Dig? Or else... ::She threatens you with her ladle.::
Now get your reekin' asses outta here, you!
::She stares at you for a few moments.:: Alright, alright, you can come in.
Wha-- How dare you, you pipe-cravin', stalagmite-ridin' yob!?
I knew you were a dumb $(#barrel-stuffer/pipe-scutchin' hooksie).
Just let us do our b-business. We won't be l-l-long.
We c-c-can't be every-where.
I c-cannot answer t-to that question.
*One* charon.
Two ch-arons.
Five char-ons.
T-t-ten charons.
Twenty ch-arons.
F-fifty charons.
One hun-dred charons.
T-two hun-dred charons and not a ch-charon more.
I'd make an offer, bu--but I'm all outta m-money.
::[Intelligence]:: Mutant-humping, shroom-assed hag!
No, y-you're a pipe-cravin', stalactite... uh, w-what was it?
Bah...
But you can be here, a-botherin' me!
I'm sure of that...
currency.sc
But that's pittance! I ain't gonna let you in for that.
Not bad, but if the thing you want is so important, then it ought to be worth some more, right?

::She pockets the coins before you even realized you gave it to her.::

Dominatin'! You're free to do your business.
currency.sc
Pipeworks-muncher!
Mut-- Whaaaaaaa--? Why you slackjaw-brained, butt-dwellin' boar snot!
Do your dirty business, you.
::[Intelligence]:: At least I am n-not a doddering, colostomy bag-for-brains m-m-mole rat!
No, you're a slackjaw-bearded... uh, what w-w-was it?

Oh, you! OH, YOU! I'll... ::Both you and Dude instinctively flinch as she raises her ladle - but she freezes in that position. After a brief pause, she returns to stirring her soup.:: Where... where'd ya learn to talk like that, $(#boy/girl)? Anyone with a tongue *that* foul, *that*... *repulsive* must've had a horrible, horrible life. Or severe brain damage. Or that truffle syndrome thing, whatever.

Poor, poor you.

::Her eyes bounce between Dude and you, and instead of wrath her face now displays pity.:: You $(#boys/folks) don't look so bad after all. You ain't no bandits, thank the chasm - you're just a pair of miserable drifters. You... a-feelin' hungry, kids? This ain't no stinky barrel soup, no - it be proper hopper stew. Bought some off Ol' Lumber for almost nothin' at all, he-he! Nothin' at all!

Want some?
Why not?
We're in a hurry, but t-thanks!
Listen, man, I too would love a bowl, but it'll sober us up - and that's not good right now, man.
Hey, man, we're just gonna take a quick look around the place, okay? We just gotta find something, like, really important. You have no idea how important, man.
Eh? You've been a-drinkin'? My late husband used to drink like a pi--
